      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Yes, see the single sentence about JDK-21 in <a href=\"https://blog.jetbrains.com/idea/2023/09/intellij-idea-2023-2-2/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">blog.jetbrains.com/idea/2023/09/intellij-idea-2023-2-2</a> :-)"
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 14363157,
      "reputation" : 853,
      "user_id" : 10374965,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ef3bd26845b5f91010d69153d28d5603?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Nicolas Othmar",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/10374965/nicolas-othmar"
    },
    "is_accepted" : true,
    "score" : 28,
    "last_activity_date" : 1696356213,
    "last_edit_date" : 1696356213,
    "creation_date" : 1695207785,
    "answer_id" : 77141759,
    "question_id" : 77141340,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I needed to update Intellij version to 2023.2.2 and change Language level (File -&gt; Project structure -&gt; project -&gt; language level) to 21 (preview)</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/4zkOj.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/4zkOj.png\" alt=\"language level 21 (preview)\" /></a>\nThe new language level won't show up until Intellij is updated to the latest version.</p>\n<p>To update Intellij, I needed to manually check for new update</p>\n<p><strong>Manually updating Intellij on Mac</strong></p>\n<p>Intellij IDEA | Check for Updates</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/ENLlm.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/ENLlm.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>Manually updating Intellij on Windows / Linux</strong></p>\n<p>File | Settings | Appearance &amp; Behavior | System Settings | Updates</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/HfSUn.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/HfSUn.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 14162458,
      "reputation" : 5331,
      "user_id" : 10231374,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://graph.facebook.com/2270515379631452/picture?type=large",
      "display_name" : "Toni",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/10231374/toni"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1701105625,
    "creation_date" : 1701105625,
    "answer_id" : 77558788,
    "question_id" : 77141340,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In addition to Nicolas' answer, if you have a Maven project you should also add the build plugin, shown below, to the <code>pom.xml</code>.</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;build&gt;\n    &lt;plugins&gt;\n        &lt;plugin&gt;\n            &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;\n            &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-compiler-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n            &lt;configuration&gt;\n                &lt;source&gt;21&lt;/source&gt;\n                &lt;target&gt;21&lt;/target&gt;\n                &lt;compilerArgs&gt;--enable-preview&lt;/compilerArgs&gt;\n            &lt;/configuration&gt;\n        &lt;/plugin&gt;\n    &lt;/plugins&gt;\n&lt;/build&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 16271965,
      "reputation" : 506,
      "user_id" : 11750273,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-WbDq4VpnSpA/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAABA/KOVIbEKbRs0/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Tejash JL",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/11750273/tejash-jl"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 9,
    "last_activity_date" : 1710395682,
    "creation_date" : 1710395682,
    "answer_id" : 78158385,
    "question_id" : 77141340,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I followed a few options mentioned above, but nothing worked.\nThe main problem was that the Gradle plugin was configured to use an older JDK version.\nI had to change it in the below settings to use JDK-21.\nAfter changing the JDK here, then everything worked fine.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/8T80f.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/8T80f.png\" alt=\"Gradle Settings\" /></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 30826163,
      "reputation" : 1,
      "user_id" : 23648374,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/2GbxO.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "cihan uluisik",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/23648374/cihan-uluisik"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1710758459,
    "last_edit_date" : 1710758459,
    "creation_date" : 1710757785,
    "answer_id" : 78179516,
    "question_id" : 77141340,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>At first I installed Oracle jdk from <a href=\"https://www.oracle.com/ae/java/technologies/downloads/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://www.oracle.com/ae/java/technologies/downloads/</a>\nand tried everything above which progressed me to the stage where compile/run/verify was working from Maven command line or plugin but not from IntelliJ ( 2023.3.4 - Community Edition).</p>\n<p>At last, re-downloading Oracle OpenJDK 21 from Intelli-J itself fixed them too.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/HjO9s.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Clicke here to see the image</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 35754864,
      "reputation" : 1,
      "user_id" : 27383895,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/73bb4d5211a81158631eb8963fa2dc99?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Zehra Bilgin",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/27383895/zehra-bilgin"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1726769206,
    "creation_date" : 1726769206,
    "answer_id" : 79003878,
    "question_id" : 77141340,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I updated the intellij idea to IntelliJ IDEA 2023.1.7 (Ultimate Edition) and reload my maven project. After that i check the Project Structure-&gt;Project Settings-&gt;Modules tab and see the modules language level is upgraded to X-Experimental feautures, and my project can be compiled.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 324398,
      "reputation" : 1367,
      "user_id" : 644949,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 14,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/9a6509513a6f7849bf471fb36699a1f2?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Vipresh",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/644949/vipresh"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1729255413,
    "creation_date" : 1729255413,
    "answer_id" : 79102141,
    "question_id" : 77141340,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I faced similar issue, I had to go and un-check &quot;Use '--release' option for cross-compilation (java 9 and later) under File &gt; Settings &gt; Build, Execution, Deployment &gt; Compiler &gt; Java Compiler</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4202987,
      "reputation" : 11,
      "user_id" : 11431627,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/eA2Gx.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "tM_za",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/11431627/tm-za"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1762786867,
    "creation_date" : 1762786867,
    "answer_id" : 79815762,
    "question_id" : 77141340,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In addition to all the answers and specifically Toni's answer , this is what worked for me - if you have a MAVEN project adding the <strong>release tag</strong>  under plugin configuration ifixed everything for me</p>\n<pre><code>            &lt;plugin&gt;\n                &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;\n                &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-compiler-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n                &lt;version&gt;3.13.0&lt;/version&gt;\n                &lt;configuration&gt;\n                    &lt;source&gt;21&lt;/source&gt;\n                    &lt;target&gt;21&lt;/target&gt;\n                    &lt;release&gt;21&lt;/release&gt;\n                &lt;/configuration&gt;\n            &lt;/plugin&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
  "owner" : {
